As per [this comment](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShellEditorServices/issues/2092#issuecomment-1773535625), the issue (at least for me) was powershell_es trying to load my powershell profile and taking to long to do it. To make Neovim not load it you only need to do the following:


```lua
      require("lspconfig").powershell_es.setup {
        bundle_path = "path/to/your/bundle_path",
        init_options = {
          enableProfileLoading = false,
        },
      }
```

Maybe it would be worth adding this to the default powershell_es config? Or some mention to it in on its documentation?
